    <p style="padding:5px 2px 5px 5px; width:550px;">The Meter Asset Loaner Program exists to cover the gap in customer service that exists when a customer must send their equipment to Sensus for repair.</p> 
    


<h5>Expectations</h5>
<p style="padding:10px 2px 5px 5px; width:550px;">Dana Kepner has made a considerable investment in time and equipment for this program.  As we make every effort to provide great customer service, the expectation is that our equipment will be returned in a timely fashion and treated with respect.</p>

<h5>Administration</h5>


	<p style="padding:10px 2px 5px 5px; width:550px;">
    Special cases notwithstanding, assets are available on a first come, first served basis.</p>
    <p style="padding:10px 2px 5px 5px; width:550px;">
    An order in SXe (aka GUI) is required to check out an asset (see below for details).</p>
    <p style="padding:10px 2px 5px 5px; width:550px;">
    The asset must be inspected and tested before delivery to the customer, and upon return from the customer.  Fill out the check out form and have the customer sign and date.  This protects you, the customer, and Kepner’s relationship with the customer.</p>
    <p style="padding:10px 2px 5px 5px; width:550px;">
    Return the asset directly to the responsible Program Administrator.  This insures that the asset is not lost/misplaced, and that the asset is available for the next customer.</p>
    

    

